{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"boolean","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions/boolean","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div style=\"background:#f5f5f5; margin: 5px 0;\" id=\"sect1\">\n    <b><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Transforming_XML_with_XSLT/The_Netscape_XSLT_XPath_Reference\">XSLT/XPath Reference</a></b>: <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Element\">XSLT elements</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/EXSLT\">EXSLT functions</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions\">XPath functions</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Axes\">XPath axes</a>\n</div>\n<p>The <code>boolean</code> function evaluates an expression and returns true or false.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token function\">boolean</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span> expression <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"arguments","title":"Arguments","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"expression\"><code>expression</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The expression to be evaluated. The expression can refer to numbers and node-sets as well as booleans.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"returns","title":"Returns","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Boolean <code>true</code> or <code>false</code> after evaluating <code>expression</code>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"notes","title":"Notes","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>A number evaluates to false if it is positive or negative zero or <code>NaN</code>. Otherwise, it evaluates true.</li>\n  <li>A node-set evaluates to true if it is non-empty.</li>\n  <li>A string evaluates to false if it an empty string. Otherwise, it evaluates to true.</li>\n  <li>An object of a type other than the four basic types is converted to a boolean in a way that is dependent on that type.</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"defined","title":"Defined","isH3":false,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/xpath#function-boolean\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">XPath 1.0 4.3</a></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"gecko_support","title":"Gecko support","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Supported.</p>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Arguments","id":"arguments"},{"text":"Returns","id":"returns"},{"text":"Notes","id":"notes"},{"text":"Defined","id":"defined"},{"text":"Gecko support","id":"gecko_support"}],"summary":"The boolean function evaluates an expression and returns true or false.","popularity":0.0007,"modified":"2021-10-08T21:06:46.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"boolean","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"boolean","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"boolean","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"boolean","locale":"pl","native":"Polski"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/xpath/functions/boolean","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/xpath/functions/boolean/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/ca43b812115fe06655700f5d0abb715da75ac808","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath","title":"XPath"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions","title":"Functions"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions/boolean","title":"boolean"}],"pageTitle":"boolean - XPath | MDN","noIndexing":false}}